The paper deals with the computational complexity of consistent answers of Boolean conjunctive queries on directed graphs, which is a topic closely related to databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves logical reasoning and complexity theory, which are relevant to the categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of first-order logic in expressing the complexity of the problem, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
